1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:02,701
Julia: <i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:02,703 --> 00:00:04,703
<i>At least it used to be,</i>

3
00:00:04,705 --> 00:00:06,705
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:06,707 --> 00:00:08,574
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:12,346 --> 00:00:15,014
<i>Invisible, indestructible,</i>

6
00:00:15,016 --> 00:00:16,582
<i>Inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:16,584 --> 00:00:18,584
We're trapped.

8
00:00:18,586 --> 00:00:21,286
Julia: <i>We don't know where</i>
<i>it came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:21,288 --> 00:00:23,555
<i>But now that we're all trapped</i>
<i>under the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:23,557 --> 00:00:25,357
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:27,561 --> 00:00:29,061
Thanks again
for letting me crash here.

12
00:00:29,063 --> 00:00:30,362
My husband isn't here,

13
00:00:30,364 --> 00:00:32,364
But he'll turn up.
You'll see, barbie.

14
00:00:34,635 --> 00:00:37,202
That thing
is never going to go away.

15
00:00:38,706 --> 00:00:41,774
Oh, no. No.

16
00:00:54,621 --> 00:00:57,790
Morning.

17
00:00:57,792 --> 00:00:59,358
Morning.

18
00:01:02,829 --> 00:01:04,530
Feeling okay?

19
00:01:04,532 --> 00:01:07,699
Yeah, it's just
a headache.

20
00:01:07,701 --> 00:01:09,802
I get them sometimes
when I'm stressed.

21
00:01:09,804 --> 00:01:11,804
Yeah, you took the last one.

22
00:01:11,806 --> 00:01:14,073
Dee's pharmacy is closed.

23
00:01:14,075 --> 00:01:15,774
Maybe the gas station
has aspirin.

24
00:01:15,776 --> 00:01:17,209
You know this town pretty well

25
00:01:17,211 --> 00:01:19,411
For someone
who's just passing through.

26
00:01:19,413 --> 00:01:21,547
Dee's is not really
a hard name to remember.

27
00:01:25,285 --> 00:01:28,120
Think I'll go over
to the radio station.

28
00:01:28,122 --> 00:01:30,189
All right, well,
I'll catch a ride with you.

29
00:01:31,791 --> 00:01:33,492
: All right,
everybody, orders are in.

30
00:01:33,494 --> 00:01:34,793
Pack it up, we're out of here.

31
00:01:36,429 --> 00:01:37,763
Man:
Hey, you can't leave!

32
00:01:42,702 --> 00:01:44,770
Back away, ollie, back away.

33
00:01:44,772 --> 00:01:46,605
This thing can really hurt you.

34
00:01:46,607 --> 00:01:48,707
Ollie:
Why is the military leaving?

35
00:01:48,709 --> 00:01:51,577
The military is
supposed to protect us.

36
00:01:51,579 --> 00:01:52,811
Linda:
Everybody, listen!

37
00:01:52,813 --> 00:01:54,246
I understand that
you're angry,

38
00:01:54,248 --> 00:01:56,248
But I'm gonna ask you
to disperse.

39
00:01:57,251 --> 00:01:59,118
Now!

40
00:02:00,286 --> 00:02:02,821
You weep for mercy

41
00:02:02,823 --> 00:02:05,858
When you've lived lives
of wickedness and pride.

42
00:02:05,860 --> 00:02:08,193
God does not hear you.

43
00:02:08,195 --> 00:02:09,728
He is the master,

44
00:02:09,730 --> 00:02:12,498
And you will bend
to his will.

45
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:14,500
Go home,
this is not helping.
"there they cry,

46
00:02:14,502 --> 00:02:17,769
"but none giveth answer
because of the pride

47
00:02:17,771 --> 00:02:19,738
Of evil men."

48
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:21,507
This dome
is his wish

49
00:02:21,509 --> 00:02:23,308
For a new eden.

50
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:24,443
What the hell's going on?

51
00:02:24,445 --> 00:02:25,511
Military's leaving.

52
00:02:25,513 --> 00:02:27,179
It's been three days
and no answers.

53
00:02:27,181 --> 00:02:28,547
Folks are getting scared.

54
00:02:28,549 --> 00:02:30,249
You think pulling a gun
is gonna reassure 'em?

55
00:02:30,251 --> 00:02:33,352
All right, all right, I don't
blame you for wanting answers.

56
00:02:33,354 --> 00:02:34,820
We all want to know when
this thing is coming down,

57
00:02:34,822 --> 00:02:36,388
But this is not helping.

58
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:37,923
Ollie: Government's
left us here to rot.

59
00:02:37,925 --> 00:02:39,858
You're a councilman, rennie.

60
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:41,393
Why should we trust you?

61
00:02:41,395 --> 00:02:45,664
Because they're out there,
ollie, and I'm in here.

62
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:47,933
Now please listen
to the sheriff.

63
00:02:47,935 --> 00:02:49,701
Soon as we know what's going on
out there, so will you.

64
00:02:49,703 --> 00:02:51,770
Go on home.

65
00:03:05,653 --> 00:03:06,652
You almost lost 'em.

66
00:03:06,654 --> 00:03:09,454
What are you gonna do--
open fire on the crowd?

67
00:03:09,456 --> 00:03:10,455
Linda?

68
00:03:10,457 --> 00:03:11,623
Whoa, excuse me.

69
00:03:11,625 --> 00:03:13,625
Is she all right?
You okay?

70
00:03:13,627 --> 00:03:15,961
Let's get out of here.
Let's get her to a car.

71
00:03:30,810 --> 00:03:32,878
Brought you some
comfortable clothes.

72
00:03:33,846 --> 00:03:36,982
And a surprise.

73
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:41,720
hmm.

74
00:03:43,823 --> 00:03:48,994
You wore this the
first time we danced.

75
00:03:48,996 --> 00:03:51,396
Junior prom.

76
00:03:51,398 --> 00:03:53,899
You were so beautiful.

77
00:03:59,539 --> 00:04:01,807
You want me to
look beautiful?

78
00:04:05,011 --> 00:04:07,279
I don't mind.

79
00:04:15,588 --> 00:04:18,724
You're starting to act
like the old angie I knew

80
00:04:18,726 --> 00:04:20,926
Before the dome
came down.

81
00:04:24,797 --> 00:04:26,865
Turn around.

82
00:04:28,801 --> 00:04:30,802
Turn around.

83
00:04:30,804 --> 00:04:32,871
I think you're
getting better.

84
00:04:34,674 --> 00:04:38,910
With trust and a little
patience, I'll get her back.

85
00:04:38,912 --> 00:04:39,911
Right, ange?

86
00:04:39,913 --> 00:04:41,280
Ange?

87
00:04:52,759 --> 00:04:54,626
Junior, I'm sorry.

88
00:04:54,628 --> 00:04:56,662
No, you're not.
No, I'm sorry.

89
00:04:59,999 --> 00:05:02,334
I should have known.

90
00:05:02,336 --> 00:05:03,735
You're not better.

91
00:05:03,737 --> 00:05:05,971
you're just
pretending.

92
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:15,847
Junior, please let me out.

93
00:05:15,849 --> 00:05:17,449
I won't tell anyone.

94
00:05:17,451 --> 00:05:19,551
I will forget
everything.

95
00:05:19,553 --> 00:05:21,053
Please, I will forget
about everything.

96
00:05:21,055 --> 00:05:23,088
Just...

97
00:05:23,090 --> 00:05:25,991
Just let me out.

98
00:05:25,993 --> 00:05:28,960
You can leave
whenever you're ready.

99
00:05:33,099 --> 00:05:35,367
But not before.

100
00:05:59,025 --> 00:06:01,093
Can I help you?

101
00:06:02,662 --> 00:06:05,697
Uh, I'm julia shumway, I'm
the editor of the weekly...

102
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:09,468
You're the lady that's been
doing the news on the radio.

103
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:10,635
That why you're
looking for phil?

104
00:06:10,637 --> 00:06:11,903
Phil?
Phil bushey,

105
00:06:11,905 --> 00:06:13,572
The dj you work with
at the station.

106
00:06:13,574 --> 00:06:15,841
That's his car;
he's got to be home.

107
00:06:15,843 --> 00:06:17,008
That's my husband's car.

108
00:06:17,010 --> 00:06:18,643
Phil!

109
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:21,146
What is all
the racket?

110
00:06:21,148 --> 00:06:22,581
What are you doing
with peter's car?

111
00:06:22,583 --> 00:06:24,049
He sold it to me.

112
00:06:25,818 --> 00:06:27,419
Oh.

113
00:06:27,421 --> 00:06:29,755
I feel like crap.

114
00:06:29,757 --> 00:06:30,722
Phil.

115
00:06:30,724 --> 00:06:32,824
I need some help!

116
00:06:32,826 --> 00:06:35,394
One seizure happens,
maybe it's no big deal.

117
00:06:35,396 --> 00:06:38,397
Two seizures in three days
buys you both a full workup.

118
00:06:38,399 --> 00:06:39,464
Mom, I feel fine.

119
00:06:39,466 --> 00:06:40,465
Yeah, me, too.

120
00:06:40,467 --> 00:06:42,567
I know, but we
have to be sure.

121
00:06:42,569 --> 00:06:45,003
Excuse me, I'm
a physician.

122
00:06:45,005 --> 00:06:46,872
We may be dealing
with something infectious

123
00:06:46,874 --> 00:06:48,173
That's causing seizures
in both of them.

124
00:06:48,175 --> 00:06:52,043
I want you to do a
blood count, an eeg,

125
00:06:52,045 --> 00:06:53,478
And if they're negative,
get them mris.

126
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,046
We can do the blood
and eeg here,

127
00:06:55,048 --> 00:06:57,582
But the closest mri is at
the big hospital in westlake,

128
00:06:57,584 --> 00:06:59,017
And that's five miles
outside of the dome.

129
00:06:59,019 --> 00:07:00,152
I don't suppose
you have a neurologist.

130
00:07:00,154 --> 00:07:02,087
We're fresh out of doctors.

131
00:07:02,089 --> 00:07:04,489
Look, one of them's
on vacation in vail,

132
00:07:04,491 --> 00:07:06,158
The other one drove his porsche
right into the dome,

133
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:09,161
Then I'll do the tests.
What kind of doctor are you?

134
00:07:09,163 --> 00:07:10,862
She's a psychiatrist,

135
00:07:10,864 --> 00:07:12,597
But she did her internship
in medicine.

136
00:07:12,599 --> 00:07:13,899
Come with me.

137
00:07:14,834 --> 00:07:16,635
Your moms are
pretty hard-core.

138
00:07:16,637 --> 00:07:17,903
You have no idea.

139
00:07:17,905 --> 00:07:20,038
All right, I'll be
right there, okay?

140
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,042
Hey, junior,

141
00:07:24,044 --> 00:07:25,610
You haven't seen
my sister, have you?

142
00:07:25,612 --> 00:07:28,180
I haven't seen her
since the dome came down.

143
00:07:28,182 --> 00:07:29,614
Angie?

144
00:07:29,616 --> 00:07:30,849
Saw her a couple
nights ago.

145
00:07:30,851 --> 00:07:31,783
Where?

146
00:07:31,785 --> 00:07:33,885
I don't know, around.

147
00:07:35,087 --> 00:07:37,556
Anything else,
little man?

148
00:07:37,558 --> 00:07:39,224
I guess not.

149
00:07:43,030 --> 00:07:46,465
She collapsed and now
she's burning up.
Junior:
Dad.

150
00:07:46,467 --> 00:07:49,201
Junior, what happened
to your hand?

151
00:07:49,203 --> 00:07:51,069
Oh, uh, chopping wood.

152
00:07:51,071 --> 00:07:53,171
Ax slipped.

153
00:07:53,173 --> 00:07:54,206
Feeling okay?

154
00:07:54,208 --> 00:07:55,907
What happened with linda?

155
00:07:55,909 --> 00:07:57,542
I don't know.

156
00:07:57,544 --> 00:07:59,744
Nurse:
We need some help.

157
00:07:59,746 --> 00:08:01,913
More people are coming in
with fever and headache.

158
00:08:01,915 --> 00:08:03,215
Big jim: What are
we dealing with here?

159
00:08:03,217 --> 00:08:04,950
I don't know, it
could be the flu.

160
00:08:04,952 --> 00:08:06,485
We need to get more cots
up from the basement.

161
00:08:06,487 --> 00:08:07,486
I'll get it.

162
00:08:07,488 --> 00:08:09,154
Junior, help barbie.

163
00:08:10,656 --> 00:08:12,224
He passed out.

164
00:08:12,226 --> 00:08:13,825
Nurse:
Put him in bay 3.

165
00:08:13,827 --> 00:08:14,993
What happened to linda?

166
00:08:14,995 --> 00:08:18,196
Probably from the same thing
that happened to phil.

167
00:08:18,198 --> 00:08:21,132
I wish I could tell
you, mrs. Shumway.

168
00:08:21,134 --> 00:08:22,968
The town's out
of doctors.

169
00:08:22,970 --> 00:08:24,536
Sure could use
your husband.

170
00:08:50,663 --> 00:08:52,664
Help!

171
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:56,668
Help! Help!

172
00:09:19,158 --> 00:09:20,692
Ow!

173
00:09:20,694 --> 00:09:22,160
Sweetheart, keep still.

174
00:09:22,162 --> 00:09:23,261
Oh, you suck at this.

175
00:09:23,263 --> 00:09:25,030
No wonder
you became a shrink.

176
00:09:25,032 --> 00:09:27,299
There, done.

177
00:09:27,301 --> 00:09:29,000
Will you run
this to the lab?

178
00:09:29,002 --> 00:09:31,570
Sure.

179
00:09:31,572 --> 00:09:34,639
So, how's this thing work?

180
00:09:34,641 --> 00:09:37,742
It measures the
electronic activity

181
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:39,911
In your brain.

182
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:42,747
Nope, you're a mutant
like wolverine.

183
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:44,249
You know x-men?

184
00:09:44,251 --> 00:09:46,084
I know a lot of stuff.

185
00:09:46,086 --> 00:09:47,319
Norrie, not now.

186
00:09:47,321 --> 00:09:49,087
Your brain's
as normal

187
00:09:49,089 --> 00:09:50,622
As any eeg I've ever seen.

188
00:09:50,624 --> 00:09:52,223
Then why'd we have the seizures?

189
00:09:52,225 --> 00:09:56,261
Alice, nurse adams
said you'd be here.

190
00:09:56,263 --> 00:09:59,097
We need your
help, right away.

191
00:10:01,334 --> 00:10:03,602
Stay.

192
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:06,938
I know this, uh,
may sound crazy,

193
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:08,206
But, uh, we're lucky
you got trapped

194
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:11,076
Here in chester's mill.

195
00:10:11,078 --> 00:10:12,677
Woman:
Excuse me.

196
00:10:15,215 --> 00:10:16,214
What's going on?

197
00:10:16,216 --> 00:10:17,816
You tell me.

198
00:10:17,818 --> 00:10:19,751
We need your help.

199
00:10:19,753 --> 00:10:22,220
Uh, well, I'll need a mask and
gloves before I examine anyone.

200
00:10:22,222 --> 00:10:23,622
We're out of both.

201
00:10:23,624 --> 00:10:24,756
What about antibiotics?

202
00:10:24,758 --> 00:10:27,392
Woman: Alice is gonna take
your temperature.

203
00:10:27,394 --> 00:10:29,661
Man:
Okay.

204
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,764
What are you doing here?

205
00:10:32,766 --> 00:10:34,766
Linda got sick,
so jim and I brought her in.

206
00:10:34,768 --> 00:10:36,101
Why? What are you doing here?

207
00:10:36,103 --> 00:10:38,336
I just brought in
a friend of yours-- phil bushey.

208
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:43,274
Go on up ahead; I'll, uh...
I'll catch up with you.

209
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:47,178
If you've never been to
chester's mill before,

210
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:48,313
How do you know phil?

211
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,650
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

212
00:10:59,393 --> 00:11:03,194
You lied to me about having
a fight with junior rennie,

213
00:11:03,196 --> 00:11:04,829
So, yeah, I thought
I would check up

214
00:11:04,831 --> 00:11:07,132
On maybe what else
you lied about.

215
00:11:07,134 --> 00:11:09,768
You owe me an explanation.

216
00:11:09,770 --> 00:11:12,303
Barbie, just tell me
the truth.

217
00:11:12,305 --> 00:11:13,905
Whoa, whoa.

218
00:11:13,907 --> 00:11:15,974
I'm okay, I just
have a headache.

219
00:11:15,976 --> 00:11:18,243
Let's get her
to the treatment area.

220
00:11:18,245 --> 00:11:21,146
Set those cots up down there;
we are getting slammed.

221
00:11:24,283 --> 00:11:26,851
Mrs. Moore?

222
00:11:28,721 --> 00:11:30,288
Linda esquivel.

223
00:11:30,290 --> 00:11:32,791
You were my third grade teacher.

224
00:11:32,793 --> 00:11:34,159
Of course.

225
00:11:34,161 --> 00:11:36,394
I remember you, linda.

226
00:11:36,396 --> 00:11:38,830
You were an amazing teacher.

227
00:11:38,832 --> 00:11:41,466
Oh. You were a terrible student.

228
00:11:43,470 --> 00:11:46,237
Do you think it's the dome?

229
00:11:46,239 --> 00:11:48,873
Is that what's making us sick?

230
00:11:50,843 --> 00:11:53,411
I don't know, mrs. Moore.

231
00:11:53,413 --> 00:11:55,847
I don't know.

232
00:11:55,849 --> 00:11:58,416
Dad, what the hell is
going on around here?

233
00:11:58,418 --> 00:12:00,418
uh, some kind of outbreak.

234
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:01,986
Doctor...

235
00:12:01,988 --> 00:12:04,022
What exactly is
going on here?

236
00:12:04,024 --> 00:12:05,824
I think it could be

237
00:12:05,826 --> 00:12:06,991
Meningitis.

238
00:12:06,993 --> 00:12:09,260
My cousin had
that. It's bad.

239
00:12:09,262 --> 00:12:11,162
One minute he was fine,
the next he was dying.

240
00:12:11,164 --> 00:12:12,497
We can't be sure,

241
00:12:12,499 --> 00:12:14,399
Because the clinic doesn't have
any spinal tap kits,

242
00:12:14,401 --> 00:12:17,102
But the symptoms--
high fever, neck pain,

243
00:12:17,104 --> 00:12:19,838
Photophobia-- I'd be surprised
if it was anything else.

244
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:22,040
I think we may have
an epidemic on our hands.

245
00:12:22,042 --> 00:12:23,141
An epidemic?

246
00:12:23,143 --> 00:12:24,175
How contagious is it?

247
00:12:24,177 --> 00:12:25,243
Very.

248
00:12:25,245 --> 00:12:26,511
If anyone who's sick coughs,

249
00:12:26,513 --> 00:12:28,246
it spreads.

250
00:12:28,248 --> 00:12:31,349
This damn dome.
It's like an incubator.

251
00:12:31,351 --> 00:12:32,784
Your son probably
got vaccinated

252
00:12:32,786 --> 00:12:34,486
When he went to college;
so did my family.

253
00:12:34,488 --> 00:12:36,521
So, we're okay.

254
00:12:36,523 --> 00:12:38,022
Yeah, I got mine
in the military.

255
00:12:38,024 --> 00:12:40,492
Yeah. Well, what about
those who didn't?

256
00:12:40,494 --> 00:12:41,960
Well, if there's no symptoms,

257
00:12:41,962 --> 00:12:43,795
Swallow an antibiotic
and you're protected.

258
00:12:43,797 --> 00:12:45,396
But for these people
who are sick,

259
00:12:45,398 --> 00:12:47,365
They need antibiotics,
and they need them fast.

260
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:50,135
Okay, so then how much time
are we talking about?

261
00:12:50,137 --> 00:12:51,302
11. maybe 12 hours.

262
00:12:51,304 --> 00:12:54,439
I checked-- we don't have
enough antibiotics

263
00:12:54,441 --> 00:12:56,307
To treat all these people.

264
00:12:56,309 --> 00:12:58,076
Dee's pharmacy.

265
00:12:58,078 --> 00:12:59,244
Listen, doctor.

266
00:12:59,246 --> 00:13:01,513
Give me a list
of what you need.

267
00:13:01,515 --> 00:13:03,982
Let me be
absolutely clear:

268
00:13:03,984 --> 00:13:06,484
If these people leave
and it spreads...

269
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:10,922
Well, we're gonna
make sure it doesn't.

270
00:13:17,096 --> 00:13:18,463
Got that list
from the doctor.

271
00:13:18,465 --> 00:13:19,564
Thanks.

272
00:13:19,566 --> 00:13:20,565
Go inside.

273
00:13:20,567 --> 00:13:23,001
Guard the door.

274
00:13:23,003 --> 00:13:24,035
Make sure no one gets out.

275
00:13:24,037 --> 00:13:25,069
Like a quarantine?

276
00:13:25,071 --> 00:13:27,138
You can call it
what you'd like.

277
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:30,275
Nobody leaves.

278
00:13:30,277 --> 00:13:33,278
Counting on you, junior.

279
00:13:40,186 --> 00:13:42,320
The clinic is now closed.

280
00:13:42,322 --> 00:13:44,956
No one leaves,
you understand?

281
00:13:46,092 --> 00:13:48,459
No one.

282
00:14:28,869 --> 00:14:30,168
Phil?

283
00:14:30,170 --> 00:14:32,136
What?

284
00:14:32,138 --> 00:14:34,606
Phil, I need to know how
you ended up with peter's car.

285
00:14:34,608 --> 00:14:37,242
Peter, I'm sorry, man, I can't
make it to the cabin tonight.

286
00:14:37,244 --> 00:14:39,510
Cabin?

287
00:14:39,512 --> 00:14:41,412
What cabin?

288
00:14:41,414 --> 00:14:42,614
What are you doing
out of bed?

289
00:14:42,616 --> 00:14:44,182
I think that he knows
where peter is.

290
00:14:44,184 --> 00:14:45,183
Uh, where my husband is.

291
00:14:45,185 --> 00:14:46,451
I just need to talk to him.

292
00:14:46,453 --> 00:14:48,119
Well, okay, give him a few hours

293
00:14:48,121 --> 00:14:50,154
For his antibiotics to kick in.

294
00:14:50,156 --> 00:14:51,589
And you should go
back to bed

295
00:14:51,591 --> 00:14:53,925
Until big jim comes back
with your dose.

296
00:14:53,927 --> 00:14:56,160
Dodee, don't go.
He's hallucinating.

297
00:14:56,162 --> 00:14:57,462
It's one of the later
symptoms of meningitis.

298
00:14:57,464 --> 00:15:00,465
That you brought him in
when you did.

299
00:15:01,433 --> 00:15:03,268
Go back to bed.

300
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:17,248
Big jim:
What the hell?

301
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:20,285
Damn it!

302
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:25,423
Whoever did this
took everything.

303
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:29,928
How many are we up to?

304
00:15:29,930 --> 00:15:32,063
At least 30
with advanced symptoms.

305
00:15:32,065 --> 00:15:35,033
Another two dozen
with early signs.

306
00:15:35,035 --> 00:15:38,169
Any news from big jim?

307
00:15:38,171 --> 00:15:40,238
Not yet.

308
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:41,472
Honey, you don't look well.

309
00:15:41,474 --> 00:15:42,707
Are you sure
you haven't caught...

310
00:15:42,709 --> 00:15:44,175
We got vaccinated,
remember?

311
00:15:44,177 --> 00:15:46,277
When we took
that safari to africa.

312
00:15:46,279 --> 00:15:48,613
I took my insulin
without eating.

313
00:15:48,615 --> 00:15:50,315
How much do you have left?

314
00:15:50,317 --> 00:15:52,250
Can we please talk
about this later?

315
00:15:52,252 --> 00:15:53,985
How much?

316
00:15:53,987 --> 00:15:55,386
Definitely a few
days' worth.

317
00:15:55,388 --> 00:15:57,689
Okay. I'm gonna get you
something to eat,

318
00:15:57,691 --> 00:15:59,090
And you're gonna eat it.

319
00:16:00,994 --> 00:16:02,727
Woman:
Dr. Calvert!

320
00:16:04,597 --> 00:16:07,265
Linda's temp's 104 and
mrs. Moore's bp's falling.

321
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:09,434
How much antibiotic
do we have left?
One dose.

322
00:16:12,705 --> 00:16:14,472
Moore:
Give linda the medicine.

323
00:16:14,474 --> 00:16:18,042
I'll wait till the next round.

324
00:16:19,211 --> 00:16:22,046
There's no way
I'm gonna take it.

325
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:29,020
Go ahead, give linda the dose.

326
00:16:49,641 --> 00:16:51,743
Man:
Uh, medical,

327
00:16:51,745 --> 00:16:52,777
This is rescue one.

328
00:16:52,779 --> 00:16:54,746
You need to let me out.
Sorry.

329
00:16:54,748 --> 00:16:56,514
Orders from my dad.

330
00:16:56,516 --> 00:16:59,017
Nobody leaves until we get
this thing under control.

331
00:16:59,019 --> 00:17:01,052
Junior?

332
00:17:02,421 --> 00:17:04,088
James?

333
00:17:04,090 --> 00:17:05,790
You don't understand.

334
00:17:05,792 --> 00:17:07,625
I think that my husband
might be in trouble.

335
00:17:07,627 --> 00:17:09,127
How?

336
00:17:10,663 --> 00:17:12,663
What...

337
00:17:12,665 --> 00:17:15,500
All I know is that

338
00:17:15,502 --> 00:17:17,735
Phil said that he was
meeting peter in a cabin.

339
00:17:17,737 --> 00:17:20,171
Like the one I found barbie at?

340
00:17:24,076 --> 00:17:26,811
What are you
talking about?

341
00:17:26,813 --> 00:17:30,081
A few days ago, I followed
barbie to this cabin.

342
00:17:30,083 --> 00:17:31,682
Uh, end of sparrow's lane.

343
00:17:31,684 --> 00:17:33,184
You need to let me out.

344
00:17:33,186 --> 00:17:36,788
I wish I could,
but... I can't.

345
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:24,802
Barbie: <i>Well, at least</i>
<i>whoever took all that medicine</i>

346
00:18:24,804 --> 00:18:25,803
<i>Couldn't have gotten far.</i>

347
00:18:25,805 --> 00:18:27,271
Because of the dome?
Yeah.

348
00:18:27,273 --> 00:18:28,673
And with a haul that size,

349
00:18:28,675 --> 00:18:30,441
There's no way
they're getting away on foot.

350
00:18:30,443 --> 00:18:33,111
So we're looking
for a truck or a van.

351
00:18:33,113 --> 00:18:34,846
Or a hearse.

352
00:18:36,448 --> 00:18:37,748
What, your reverend?

353
00:18:39,885 --> 00:18:42,120
The hell would he
be doing with drugs?

354
00:18:42,122 --> 00:18:44,188
Nothing good.

355
00:18:47,459 --> 00:18:52,497
His wrath burns like fire.

356
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:04,909
The hell are you doing?

357
00:19:06,411 --> 00:19:07,845
Honoring his plan.

358
00:19:07,847 --> 00:19:09,847
When I heard
folks got sick,

359
00:19:09,849 --> 00:19:10,848
I broke into dee's pharmacy...

360
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:12,450
What are you, insane?!

361
00:19:12,452 --> 00:19:13,818
People will die
without that medicine!

362
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:15,920
Those people
are supposed to die.

363
00:19:15,922 --> 00:19:17,355
It's god's plan.

364
00:19:17,357 --> 00:19:19,190
Trust me.

365
00:19:19,192 --> 00:19:22,527
Who lives and dies
under his dome.

366
00:19:22,529 --> 00:19:23,761
And there's nothing
you can do about it.

367
00:19:23,763 --> 00:19:25,696
Unload the car.

368
00:19:36,176 --> 00:19:38,376
What's happening?

369
00:19:38,378 --> 00:19:41,679
They gave you
antibiotics.

370
00:19:41,681 --> 00:19:43,881
You should be
on the mend soon.

371
00:19:48,353 --> 00:19:49,854
And how are you feeling?

372
00:19:49,856 --> 00:19:52,757
I've been better.

373
00:19:52,759 --> 00:19:55,193
If you told me yesterday

374
00:19:55,195 --> 00:19:58,596
That the idea
of junior rennie

375
00:19:58,598 --> 00:20:01,933
Brandishing a shotgun
would be reassuring...

376
00:20:02,936 --> 00:20:06,604
...I'd have laughed
my head off.

377
00:20:06,606 --> 00:20:10,474
Actually, I might have
said that about you

378
00:20:10,476 --> 00:20:12,376
A few years ago.

379
00:20:12,378 --> 00:20:14,979
Wasn't exactly
the teacher's pet, was I?

380
00:20:14,981 --> 00:20:17,982
With that mouth of yours?

381
00:20:17,984 --> 00:20:20,418
lord, no.

382
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:25,723
But now look at you.

383
00:20:25,725 --> 00:20:28,960
The town sheriff.

384
00:20:28,962 --> 00:20:31,529
I've had a lot
of help, though.

385
00:20:31,531 --> 00:20:33,764
Especially from duke perkins.

386
00:20:33,766 --> 00:20:36,234
May he rest in peace.

387
00:20:39,805 --> 00:20:42,673
But don't sell yourself short.

388
00:20:50,617 --> 00:20:52,416
Mrs. Moore?

389
00:20:53,419 --> 00:20:54,418
Mrs. Moore?

390
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:57,622
Help! We need help in here!

391
00:20:59,424 --> 00:21:00,992
She's coding.

392
00:21:00,994 --> 00:21:01,926
Starting chest
compressions.

393
00:21:01,928 --> 00:21:03,327
One, two,

394
00:21:03,329 --> 00:21:06,364
Three, four, five,
six, seven, eight,

395
00:21:06,366 --> 00:21:07,865
Nine, ten, 11. 12...

396
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:09,934
I was just talking to her.

397
00:21:35,295 --> 00:21:37,295
Ollie:
Out of the way, junior!

398
00:21:37,297 --> 00:21:40,431
Man: You have no right
to keep us here.

399
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:42,333
Ollie: You can't stop all of us
with that gun.

400
00:21:42,335 --> 00:21:43,734
Step back.

401
00:21:43,736 --> 00:21:45,870
Woman: Whoa!
Man: Hey, hey, hey.

402
00:21:46,906 --> 00:21:47,672
Let's go.

403
00:21:51,511 --> 00:21:53,611
Junior.

404
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:16,334
Mr. Densmore...

405
00:22:16,336 --> 00:22:19,470
You remember
when my mother died?

406
00:22:20,439 --> 00:22:22,873
And your wife,
she made that amazing

407
00:22:22,875 --> 00:22:25,376
Corn bread.

408
00:22:25,378 --> 00:22:28,045
From your own field, she said.

409
00:22:28,047 --> 00:22:30,781
Even gave me the skillet.

410
00:22:33,652 --> 00:22:35,486
I remember.

411
00:22:35,488 --> 00:22:37,488
Now I'm in here...

412
00:22:37,490 --> 00:22:41,392
With you, with this.

413
00:22:41,394 --> 00:22:44,028
Not to point
a gun at you.

414
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:46,564
But because I live here

415
00:22:46,566 --> 00:22:49,133
And I'm one of you.

416
00:22:53,905 --> 00:22:56,540
We've got to fight
through this thing together

417
00:22:56,542 --> 00:23:00,544
And trust that we're
all in here for a reason.

418
00:23:00,546 --> 00:23:02,480
I believe in this town.

419
00:23:02,482 --> 00:23:04,882
I believe in my dad.

420
00:23:04,884 --> 00:23:07,752
And I believe in you.

421
00:24:04,910 --> 00:24:07,645
Oh, peter.

422
00:24:31,203 --> 00:24:33,204
This is all I could
scrounge up.

423
00:24:33,206 --> 00:24:34,872
It's a zoo out there.

424
00:24:34,874 --> 00:24:36,941
Thanks.

425
00:24:39,077 --> 00:24:42,079
So what are we gonna do when we
run out of, like, peanut butter

426
00:24:42,081 --> 00:24:43,747
And jelly and bread?

427
00:24:43,749 --> 00:24:44,915
What are we gonna eat?

428
00:24:44,917 --> 00:24:46,750
We'll get out before then.

429
00:24:47,719 --> 00:24:50,788
All right, so, I was thinking...

430
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:52,490
Our seizures.

431
00:24:52,492 --> 00:24:55,125
The last time one happened
was after we touched.

432
00:24:55,127 --> 00:24:57,595
Yeah, could've been
a coincidence.

433
00:24:57,597 --> 00:24:58,596
Both of us?

434
00:24:58,598 --> 00:25:01,866
At the same exact time?

435
00:25:05,238 --> 00:25:07,505
What if we triggered it?

436
00:25:07,507 --> 00:25:09,240
Okay, how would
that happen?

437
00:25:09,242 --> 00:25:11,108
I don't know, but...

438
00:25:11,110 --> 00:25:12,643
We should test it.

439
00:25:12,645 --> 00:25:14,645
Like...

440
00:25:14,647 --> 00:25:17,281
Touch again?

441
00:25:18,250 --> 00:25:19,650
Yeah.

442
00:25:19,652 --> 00:25:22,520
Unless, you know, you're scared.

443
00:25:22,522 --> 00:25:24,989
No, I'm not scared.

444
00:25:24,991 --> 00:25:27,525
We should film it.

445
00:25:27,527 --> 00:25:29,693
Here. Get on the floor.

446
00:25:29,695 --> 00:25:30,761
All right.

447
00:25:30,763 --> 00:25:32,263
But if you pee your pants,

448
00:25:32,265 --> 00:25:34,665
Just know there will be
video evidence.

449
00:25:34,667 --> 00:25:36,600
Joe:
Same goes for you.

450
00:25:43,609 --> 00:25:44,909
You ready?

451
00:25:44,911 --> 00:25:46,810
Let's do it.

452
00:25:57,789 --> 00:26:00,591
Okay. I feel stupid.

453
00:26:07,300 --> 00:26:09,767
Got the antibiotics.

454
00:26:09,769 --> 00:26:11,669
Man: Bring it straight on
in to the charge nurse.

455
00:26:14,139 --> 00:26:16,307
Any problems in there?

456
00:26:16,309 --> 00:26:17,908
Not at all.

457
00:26:23,950 --> 00:26:26,684
Help!

458
00:26:26,686 --> 00:26:29,119
Junior!

459
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:43,968
So, where's julia?

460
00:26:46,638 --> 00:26:48,772
Not a clue, man.

461
00:26:48,774 --> 00:26:51,342
I barely know where I am.

462
00:26:53,645 --> 00:26:56,046
What did you tell her?

463
00:27:08,727 --> 00:27:10,628
What did she ask you?
It's all kind of blurry,

464
00:27:10,630 --> 00:27:11,762
But I think it was something
about her husband.

465
00:27:11,764 --> 00:27:13,631
Relax, it's not like

466
00:27:13,633 --> 00:27:15,332
He's gonna say
anything about you. He's gone.

467
00:27:17,235 --> 00:27:19,236
What do you mean, he's gone?

468
00:27:19,238 --> 00:27:20,704
Gone like gone.

469
00:27:20,706 --> 00:27:22,806
Like "adios, peter shumway."

470
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:31,048
About a month ago, he came to me
asking if I knew any hit men.

471
00:27:31,050 --> 00:27:32,716
Whoa...

472
00:27:32,718 --> 00:27:34,284
He asked you about hit men?

473
00:27:34,286 --> 00:27:35,953
I know. Right?

474
00:27:35,955 --> 00:27:39,289
And I told him that crap
was only in the movies.

475
00:27:39,291 --> 00:27:41,392
He was in a bad way.

476
00:27:41,394 --> 00:27:43,794
He sold me his
car for a steal.

477
00:27:43,796 --> 00:27:46,163
I told him if things
were that bad, he should

478
00:27:46,165 --> 00:27:48,799
Take the cash and buy the
first bus ticket out of here

479
00:27:48,801 --> 00:27:50,901
And start over.

480
00:27:50,903 --> 00:27:53,771
Sorry, man. I don't know
how much he owed you.

481
00:27:54,974 --> 00:27:57,274
You ain't getting
that cash back.

482
00:27:58,276 --> 00:28:02,246
And how much of this
did you tell her?

483
00:28:03,214 --> 00:28:05,215
It's tough to say. I...

484
00:28:05,217 --> 00:28:06,750
I was pretty out of it.

485
00:28:25,070 --> 00:28:26,470
Peter?

486
00:28:29,941 --> 00:28:31,942
Hey there, red.

487
00:28:33,813 --> 00:28:35,813
Why didn't you tell me?

488
00:28:35,815 --> 00:28:38,849
I'll tell you soon.

489
00:28:49,127 --> 00:28:52,096
Norrie. Wake up.

490
00:28:52,098 --> 00:28:54,832
You feel anything?

491
00:28:54,834 --> 00:28:56,967
I don't remember.

492
00:28:56,969 --> 00:28:59,069
Let's check out the video.

493
00:28:59,071 --> 00:29:01,171
I'll rewind it.

494
00:29:03,309 --> 00:29:05,375
Here we go.

495
00:29:10,415 --> 00:29:12,750
Norrie:
Okay. I feel stupid.

496
00:29:14,286 --> 00:29:16,754
Both:
The pink stars are falling.

497
00:29:16,756 --> 00:29:19,323
The pink stars
are falling in lines.

498
00:29:19,325 --> 00:29:21,992
Pink stars?

499
00:29:21,994 --> 00:29:23,494
I don't get it.

500
00:29:23,496 --> 00:29:25,763
Shh...

501
00:29:27,932 --> 00:29:30,934
Do you remember doing that?

502
00:29:30,936 --> 00:29:32,169
No.

503
00:29:32,171 --> 00:29:33,537
No way.

504
00:29:33,539 --> 00:29:35,539
What does this mean?

505
00:29:35,541 --> 00:29:37,875
I don't know.

506
00:29:37,877 --> 00:29:39,443
Maybe we're not supposed
to tell anyone.

507
00:29:39,445 --> 00:29:41,912
Why not?

508
00:29:41,914 --> 00:29:45,215
Joe:
Norrie. Wake up.

509
00:29:45,217 --> 00:29:46,950
'cause the dome
doesn't want us to.

510
00:29:46,952 --> 00:29:47,951
Norrie:
What happened?

511
00:29:47,953 --> 00:29:50,921
Joe:
You feel anything?

512
00:29:56,861 --> 00:29:58,562
Hey. Have you seen julia?

513
00:29:58,564 --> 00:29:59,563
Junior:
Why?

514
00:29:59,565 --> 00:30:01,899
Did she wise up and ditch you?

515
00:30:01,901 --> 00:30:04,902
When's the last time
you saw her?

516
00:30:04,904 --> 00:30:06,904
Couple hours ago.

517
00:30:06,906 --> 00:30:08,872
She kept asking about a cabin.

518
00:30:11,042 --> 00:30:12,376
What'd you tell her?

519
00:30:12,378 --> 00:30:15,979
I just mentioned the place
I saw you a couple days ago.

520
00:30:15,981 --> 00:30:17,281
Give me the keys to your truck.

521
00:30:17,283 --> 00:30:19,283
No.
Hey.

522
00:30:19,285 --> 00:30:22,152
Now, she left
on your watch.

523
00:30:22,154 --> 00:30:25,155
She's sick
and she will die out there,

524
00:30:25,157 --> 00:30:28,125
So give me the keys
to your truck.

525
00:30:48,847 --> 00:30:50,514
Peter...

526
00:31:17,408 --> 00:31:20,911
All right. You were a brave
little girl back there.

527
00:31:20,913 --> 00:31:22,446
Okay. Get home
and get better.

528
00:31:22,448 --> 00:31:23,614
She's good.

529
00:31:23,616 --> 00:31:25,883
Oh. Well, well, well.

530
00:31:25,885 --> 00:31:28,619
Look who came back
from the dead.

531
00:31:28,621 --> 00:31:30,621
I heard you saved the day.

532
00:31:30,623 --> 00:31:33,223
Well, that's what I do.

533
00:31:33,225 --> 00:31:35,559
Well, your son takes
after you, too.

534
00:31:35,561 --> 00:31:37,427
Oh, yeah?

535
00:31:37,429 --> 00:31:41,131
He stopped what could
have been a full-blown riot.

536
00:31:45,069 --> 00:31:48,238
People were freaking out,
and he talked them down.

537
00:31:50,241 --> 00:31:53,577
Chip off the old block.

538
00:31:58,249 --> 00:32:02,119
You ever consider
a career in law enforcement?

539
00:32:20,939 --> 00:32:23,073
Was that you?

540
00:32:27,111 --> 00:32:29,379
Was that me what?

541
00:32:30,682 --> 00:32:34,284
Was that you who saved my life?

542
00:32:44,162 --> 00:32:47,531
I learned about peter
in that cabin.

543
00:32:52,136 --> 00:32:55,072
We're broke;
he emptied our accounts.

544
00:32:57,575 --> 00:33:00,711
And the house is
in foreclosure.

545
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:06,583
So, what were you all into?

546
00:33:06,585 --> 00:33:08,251
Drugs?

547
00:33:15,426 --> 00:33:19,429
When I got out of the military,
I did, um...

548
00:33:19,431 --> 00:33:22,032
I had a bunch of odd jobs.

549
00:33:22,034 --> 00:33:25,402
Uh... Was a line cook.

550
00:33:25,404 --> 00:33:27,404
Construction.

551
00:33:28,674 --> 00:33:32,009
And then, um...

552
00:33:32,011 --> 00:33:34,478
Then I linked up
with a bookie...

553
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:36,580
Out of westlake.

554
00:33:38,516 --> 00:33:40,650
Taking bets?

555
00:33:42,620 --> 00:33:46,289
Making sure the people
paid what they owed.

556
00:33:50,161 --> 00:33:52,162
You're an enforcer.

557
00:33:52,164 --> 00:33:55,532
Guys like phil owed...

558
00:33:55,534 --> 00:33:57,200
And they paid up,

559
00:33:57,202 --> 00:34:00,203
And most of the time,
it's like that.

560
00:34:00,205 --> 00:34:02,272
Peter never gambled.

561
00:34:18,222 --> 00:34:20,757
Peter : I've got
the cash, but my wife's home.

562
00:34:20,759 --> 00:34:22,559
Meet me at the other spot.

563
00:34:25,063 --> 00:34:27,831
It's his voice mail
from five days ago.

564
00:34:30,134 --> 00:34:32,602
So, where is he now?

565
00:34:33,571 --> 00:34:35,639
Please.

566
00:34:39,177 --> 00:34:41,244
I have to know.

567
00:34:47,151 --> 00:34:49,319
He must have taken off.

568
00:34:50,088 --> 00:34:52,155
You know, that
happens sometimes.

569
00:34:52,157 --> 00:34:56,093
Some of these guys, they
get in so deep, and...

570
00:34:56,095 --> 00:34:58,829
You know, they
skip town.

571
00:35:04,769 --> 00:35:07,170
I'm sorry.

572
00:35:07,172 --> 00:35:10,107
You're sorry?

573
00:35:14,612 --> 00:35:17,280
I let you stay in my house.

574
00:35:19,484 --> 00:35:22,519
I trusted you.

575
00:35:25,289 --> 00:35:27,624
Your sorry means nothing to me.

576
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:32,629
When I get back home,
you better be gone.

577
00:35:39,270 --> 00:35:41,271
Norrie: So, is
the outbreak over?

578
00:35:41,273 --> 00:35:43,240
Well, everyone who's sick
has been treated,

579
00:35:43,242 --> 00:35:45,408
And anyone exposed
to meningitis...

580
00:35:45,410 --> 00:35:46,910
Got antibiotics.

581
00:35:46,912 --> 00:35:48,912
So yes, it's over.

582
00:35:48,914 --> 00:35:51,715
How do you guys feel?
Any more seizures?

583
00:35:51,717 --> 00:35:53,450
No. We're fine.

584
00:35:55,219 --> 00:35:56,653
What have you two
been doing all day?

585
00:35:56,655 --> 00:35:58,688
Oh, you know, just
making out and stuff.

586
00:35:58,690 --> 00:36:00,223
Alice:
Right.

587
00:36:00,225 --> 00:36:02,259
It's the "stuff" that
usually worries us.

588
00:36:02,261 --> 00:36:04,227
I am beat.

589
00:36:04,229 --> 00:36:05,896
Can we go home, please?

590
00:36:05,898 --> 00:36:07,664
Norrie:
Home?

591
00:36:07,666 --> 00:36:09,299
It's a room
above a diner.

592
00:36:09,301 --> 00:36:11,635
You have
any better ideas, kiddo?

593
00:36:11,637 --> 00:36:13,637
Well, I do.

594
00:36:13,639 --> 00:36:16,239
I mean, both my parents
are outside the dome,

595
00:36:16,241 --> 00:36:18,475
And there's more than
enough room at my house.

596
00:36:18,477 --> 00:36:22,245
It's just me, so...
You guys could stay there.

597
00:36:22,247 --> 00:36:24,881
Please don't say no.

598
00:36:24,883 --> 00:36:26,383
Please?

599
00:36:29,287 --> 00:36:31,855
Thanks, joe.
That'd be great.

600
00:36:31,857 --> 00:36:34,724
Carolyn: I'll grab our stuff
and meet you in the car.

601
00:36:44,235 --> 00:36:46,303
♪

602
00:36:55,246 --> 00:36:57,781
Babe, what are you doing?

603
00:37:01,953 --> 00:37:04,354
Are you stealing insulin?

604
00:37:07,325 --> 00:37:10,660
You yourself said you only
had a week's supply left.

605
00:37:10,662 --> 00:37:13,730
Alice, look what
happened today.

606
00:37:13,732 --> 00:37:16,833
We almost ran out of
antibiotics for everyone.

607
00:37:16,835 --> 00:37:18,568
What happens
when <i>we</i> run out?

608
00:37:18,570 --> 00:37:19,669
Okay, what's going on?

609
00:37:19,671 --> 00:37:22,305
You're not acting like yourself.

610
00:37:25,509 --> 00:37:28,612
I-I'm scared.

611
00:37:28,614 --> 00:37:31,681
What if the dome lasts forever?

612
00:37:33,651 --> 00:37:36,419
It won't.

613
00:37:36,421 --> 00:37:38,455
We will get out of here.

614
00:37:38,457 --> 00:37:41,992
Soon.

615
00:37:41,994 --> 00:37:44,394
I promise.

616
00:37:58,009 --> 00:38:00,443
You sure
you'll be okay?

617
00:38:00,445 --> 00:38:01,911
Yeah.

618
00:38:03,848 --> 00:38:05,682
Thanks for the ride.

619
00:38:05,684 --> 00:38:08,285
Yeah.

620
00:38:08,287 --> 00:38:10,854
it's not
your fault, you know.

621
00:38:10,856 --> 00:38:12,756
What isn't?

622
00:38:12,758 --> 00:38:14,491
Mrs. Moore.

623
00:38:17,461 --> 00:38:20,397
She died saving my life.

624
00:38:24,502 --> 00:38:28,471
She knew how important
you are to this town.

625
00:38:28,473 --> 00:38:30,307
To all of us.

626
00:38:30,309 --> 00:38:33,810
I'm not the only one.

627
00:38:33,812 --> 00:38:37,047
What you did today
saved a lot of lives.

628
00:38:37,049 --> 00:38:40,483
The way you did it.

629
00:38:40,485 --> 00:38:42,319
Duke always said

630
00:38:42,321 --> 00:38:44,888
The greatest weapon
we have as police

631
00:38:44,890 --> 00:38:46,790
Is a good heart.

632
00:38:54,965 --> 00:38:56,866
Mrs. Moore was right.

633
00:38:58,636 --> 00:39:00,470
About what?

634
00:39:00,472 --> 00:39:02,806
We   <i>hav</i>come a long way.

635
00:39:34,739 --> 00:39:36,773
If you came here
to apologize,

636
00:39:36,775 --> 00:39:38,007
Don't bother.

637
00:39:38,009 --> 00:39:40,610
I have nothing
to apologize for.

638
00:39:40,612 --> 00:39:43,480
I came... To
give you this.

639
00:39:45,082 --> 00:39:47,584
My share of
the profits.

640
00:39:47,586 --> 00:39:49,753
Keep all the propane.

641
00:39:49,755 --> 00:39:53,790
I'm gonna wash my hands of
our dirty little business.

642
00:39:55,861 --> 00:39:57,894
Little late for that, lester.

643
00:39:57,896 --> 00:39:59,929
Never too late
to repent.

644
00:39:59,931 --> 00:40:02,399
You think you've
saved this town,

645
00:40:02,401 --> 00:40:04,401
But you've damned them.

646
00:40:04,403 --> 00:40:06,403
You defied god's will.

647
00:40:06,405 --> 00:40:09,506
And for that, you'll pay.

648
00:40:09,508 --> 00:40:11,408
You're lucky I didn't
haul your ass into jail

649
00:40:11,410 --> 00:40:13,576
For what you did today.

650
00:40:13,578 --> 00:40:15,111
Luck has nothing to do with it.

651
00:40:15,113 --> 00:40:17,781
You can't hurt me
without hurting yourself.

652
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:20,750
God bless.

653
00:40:39,938 --> 00:40:41,538
Help!

654
00:40:41,540 --> 00:40:43,506
Help...!

655
00:40:43,508 --> 00:40:45,041
Help!

656
